  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations to Illinois are $7.7B in FY2026 to date. Award activity so far includes 331,046 awards with an average award size of $23.2K. Obligations fell 37.9% year over year. Recent fiscal years show higher totals, with FY21 at $12B, FY22 at $13.6B, FY23 at $13B, FY24 at $13.4B, and FY25 at $12.4B. The Department of Defense accounts for the largest share of FY2026 obligations at $3.7B, followed by the Department of Energy at $1.6B and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $1.5B. Research and development and medical supply industries lead by dollar amount, and the largest individual vendors include UCHICAGO ARGONNE, LLC at $907M and W S DARLEY & CO at $747M. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What changed in FY2026 compared with prior years?",
        "body": "Obligations in FY2026 to date are $7.7B, down 37.9% year over year. This FY2026 total is lower than each of the prior five fiscal years, which ranged from $12B in FY21 to $13.6B in FY22. The count of awards for FY2026 to date is 331,046 with an average award size of $23.2K. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date)."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, industries, and vendors dominate Illinois federal contracting?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense is the largest buyer at $3.7B, followed by the Department of Energy at $1.6B and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $1.5B. Leading industries by obligations include Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences at $907M and Medical, Dental, and Hospital Equipment and Supplies Merchant Wholesalers at $882M. Top vendors include UCHICAGO ARGONNE, LLC at $907M, W S DARLEY & CO at $747M, and MEDLINE INDUSTRIES, LP at $691M. These amounts reflect FY2026 to date obligations."
      }
    ]
  },
